Class Node<T>

java.lang.Object
Node<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Buffer type for the node
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
Direct Known Subclasses:
AmazonWebServer, DeliveryTruck, Section, ShippingCenter, ShippingDock
public abstract class Node<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
A node consists of a single input buffer and 1 or more output buffers. A node starts processing when the run() is called
Author:
Wil Simpson
